quran[17]{c,v,t}:
  23,1,"Surely the believers have attained success:"
  23,2,"those who are reverent in their prayers;"
  23,3,"and those who disregard idle talk;"
  23,4,"and those who are observant of the purifying charity{1};",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is zakāt, which denotes purification and growth.
  23,5,"and those who preserve their private parts,"
  23,6,"except from their spouses or those whom they rightfully possess—for then they are free from blame."
  23,7,"But whoever seeks anything beyond that—those are the transgressors."
  23,8,"And those who to <span class=""h"">their trusts<sup foot_note=""80625"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>and their covenant are faithful,"
  23,9,"and those who preserve <span class=""h"">their prayers<sup foot_note=""80626"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>—"
  23,10,"those are the ones who are the<i class=""s"">(true) </i>inheritors"
  23,11,"who inherit Paradise; therein they abide."
  23,12,"And most surely, We created man from an extract of clay;"
  23,13,"then We made him a sperm-drop, lodged in a secure place;"
  23,14,"then We developed the sperm-drop into a clinging form, and We developed the clinging form into a morsel-like lump, and We developed the morsel-like lump into <span class=""h"">bones<sup foot_note=""80627"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, and We clothed the <span class=""h"">bones</span><a class=""sup""><sup>d </sup></a>with flesh, then We produced him into another creation. So supremely blessed be Allah, the Best of creators."
  23,15,"Then after that you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>are surely bound to die."
  23,16,"Then on the Day of Resurrection you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>are bound to be raised."
  23,17,"And surely We created above you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>seven<i class=""s"">(heavenly) </i>roads, and never have We been oblivious of the creation."
